President Moon of the Republic of Korea thanked President Trump for his dedication and effort in safeguarding peace and freedom in the region. This visit marks the first time in history that the presidents of both countries have visited the demilitarized zone. The Joint Security Area is being transformed from a symbol of confrontation to a symbol of peace, thanks to President Trump's efforts. President Trump expressed his appreciation for the special group of people in attendance and mentioned his scheduled meeting with Chairman Kim of North Korea. He received a gift from General Abrams, a golfer's utility tool with his name and the commands of the United Nations, Combined Forces, and US Forces Korea. The motto of the ROK-US alliance, "We Go Together," was emphasized. President Trump thanked everyone and shook hands with some of the heroes present.